annotation.TEXT: Now here, be very careful. The saws become invisible when they sink into the water, but they can still hurt you. Also, there are fireballs to worry about too.
Gotta check every pipe, like usual, even if I know that they don't go anywhere...
Oh, I just noticed, these Yoshi coins reappear as well. Not just the ones needed for the puzzle. So, you can always get 5 Yoshi coins per visit.
Now, these are somewhat tricky jumps, so if you have a cape, you might want to use it.
ok I'll watch out for veri chalanging level here now. Oh, and I'll be sure to watch for bugs or other insects in this game too! If any of you guys spot any, let him know!
Demo count: 17
Oh, there's actually something over here! A P-switch and a door! Looks like remnants of the original SMW to me though, but let's see if anything interesting happens here.
Whoa, just barely avoided getting my head burned there.
That's pretty interesting... Maybe there'll be a way to reach a normal exit in this place yet!
(Yeah, they're still called "SomeGuy712x", because nobody got the minimum 2 votes needed to win this time.)
Still nothing, and through this door...
I'm pretty sure I can hit that bouncing box if I aim my fireballs just right...

Now, I can think of one other possibility for reaching a normal exit, but that would require getting the P-switch on the left side of this area over here, and unfortunately, it seems to be trapped in its chamber on the left. Nuts...
Hello, and welcome back to Chaos CompleXX! You may be wondering why I'm back here again...
But, what about all of this unexplored land over... here...?
How come Mario can't do these fancy jump kicks during normal gameplay? Maybe they were initially planned for this game, but ultimately scrapped until Super Mario 64...
Okay, why have I suddenly started to play sloppily again?
Okay, now aim carefully...
Hey, is that a MOON I see down there? It is! Sweet! Yeah, you might miss that if you scroll the screen up too fast here.
Yeah, these turn blocks aren't breakable, so they must be holding something. I'll try to remember to check them later.
Oh, well. Let's get back to the main quest.

And in this block, we find wings. Yeah, the same kind of wings and bonus area that you can much more easily obtain a little later in the level, so don't bother with these unless you're trying to speed run the game.
Nothing!
Argh! Bad jump...
To be continued...
Alright, it's boss time! It looks like Morton, and it smells like Morton...
Oh, and the upper route here just contains some coins. Nothing too important, but there's nothing stopping you from having both the coins and the MOOOONNN!!!
Yes, I must win to play next level! Well said!
Whoa! Wow, how did I manage to escape that predicament?
Alright, here we go again. This will be tougher without power ups...
Be careful of the bouncing boxes. You can stomp them, and they're flammable and cape-spinnable, so you've got plenty of attack options against them.
Wait, finale world? You mean there's only three worlds?
Oh, man. Without any power ups, this part could be tough.
We just end up back here again...
It also dies like Morton, so it's either Morton, or his long lost identical twin named "boss" that I've never seen before.
Yep, that's probably why there's a "3" on top of Bowser's castle, because this really is the last world, which I'll begin making my way through next time!
Yes, I am superplayer. Would you like frinds with that?
Oh, wait! This isn't the same room that I initially started the level in! It's a copy of the original SMW level, which hasn't been edited at all!
Rats. It just sends me back to familiar territory. Well, at least I can get another MOON and the recurring Yoshi coins again.
And, back here again, I'm going to try doing some tool-assisted flight under the level to the left. I'll bring a key with me, just in case it's needed.
What?! There were TWO surprise saws?! Oh, man... I can't believe I fell for the double surprise saw trick!
The 1-up block there has already turned brown, probably due to me collecting something in one of the previous rooms that had the same item memory index. And through this door...
Oh, yeah. What are inside of these unbreakable turn blocks?
Oh, hey, the MOOOOONNNN came back for me to collect again!
Got it! Alright!
Huh. I guess there aren't any more lands to explore besides the one I'm about to enter. (Unless that lone ghost in the ocean is hiding something...)
Now did it decide to go for the legendary triple surprise saw trick? ...No? I guess they could only handle two (which was still enough to kill me last time).
Whoa, careful! Hey, those turn blocks aren't breakable? Didn't know that. I wonder what's inside of them then. Maybe I'll check later...
Good!
Alright, so we've got a boss level to take on! Let's do this!
In this part, if you're good, you might be able to spin jump off the saws before they sink too far into the water.
Okay, now, you're not tricking me here again, game! I'm on to you!
Haw, haw!
Either way, that battle was over in a flash, with me being victorious!
Demo count: Time paradox
Dodge the saw blades and Thwomps here, but don't be too hasty in climbing up...
Okay, now those spikes you see up there... They're fake, and so is the ceiling, so don't worry too much about how high you jump or fly here.
Nothing up above, but what if I hit the P-switch?
Haw, haw!
Alright, now this part with the Thwomps is easier, especially since one of them decided to be a blockhead and park himself directly over a lava pit!

Well, SuperSupermario24 mentioned to me that I could've used a glitched SomeGuy712x shell to hit this invisible block up ahead, and I'm like "But of course! Why didn't I think of that? Especially since I did this trick before in Rosa Perplex 1!"
Okay, we're nearing the boss, but watch out for a surprise saw blade as you approach the boss door.
